<recipe>
    <name>Persian Eggplant With Tomatoes and Potatoes (Yateamche Bademjon)</name>
    <indexCharacter>P</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>1. Peel and cut eggplants into approximately 1” cubes. Put into a large bowl with 1 T salt and water to cover for 15-20 minutes.

2.  Peel and cut potatoes into approximately ½” cubes. Put into a large bowl with water to cover.

3. Dice the onion and press the garlic cloves.

4. Dice the tomatoes.

5. Add oil to large pan and heat to medium.  Add onions and sauté.

6. After the onions have sautéd for 2-3 minutes add the garlic.

7. After another 2-3 minutes add the potatoes, turmeric and black pepper.  Sauté for another 3 minutes.

8. Drain and rinse eggplant, and add to the pan along with the salt.

9. Dice and de-seed ½ of the serrano pepper and add to the pan.  Then add the tomato paste.  After 1-2 minutes add the tomatoes.

10. Cover and reduce temperature to simmer for 10-15 minutes. Check for moisture.  If needed add 1/4-1/2 cup of water.  Simmer for another 10-15 minutes.</instructions>
